egulation. Additionally, CSF is studied for its involvement in glutamate function, particularly in patients with schizophrenia, suggesting its significance in understanding the neurochemical basis of this disorder. Together, these findings underscore the importance of cerebrospinal fluid in both behavioral and psychiatric research.", "CHANGSHA:Changsha is the city in China where the Children's Adaptive Behavior Rating Scale was developed in 1990", "CHARCOT:A 19th-century neurologist who emphasized the role of suggestion and self-suggestion in the development of hysteria", "CHECKLIST FOR AUTISM IN TODDLERS (CHAT):A screening tool used to identify early signs of autism in toddlers", "CHENGDU:A city in China where a 1959 survey on neurasthenia prevalence was conducted"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}